01:08:37,820 --> 01:08:40,660
just because we can do it doesn't mean we want to do it.

1321
01:08:40,660 --> 01:08:41,700
But in this case, yeah,

1322
01:08:41,700 --> 01:08:44,300
of course we would want to use all that new technology

1323
01:08:44,300 --> 01:08:46,100
to make the adjustment process.

1324
01:08:47,100 --> 01:08:48,700
You want to adjust for details,

1325
01:08:48,700 --> 01:08:51,260
you want to adjust for unseen events.

1326
01:08:51,260 --> 01:08:52,820
And if we've got new technologies

1327
01:08:52,820 --> 01:08:55,220
that would make all that easier and more efficient,

1328
01:08:55,220 --> 01:08:57,740
of course that makes the whole thing work better.

1329
01:08:57,740 --> 01:09:00,060
We should be very happy about that.

1330
01:09:00,060 --> 01:09:03,620
So now we have actually transformed

1331
01:09:03,620 --> 01:09:06,700
these aggregated information

1332
01:09:06,700 --> 01:09:10,100
into aggregated pieces for production,

1333
01:09:10,100 --> 01:09:11,300
inputs for production,

1334
01:09:11,300 --> 01:09:15,420
and they have been transformed into detailed products

1335
01:09:15,420 --> 01:09:17,380
by the workers councils.

1336
01:09:17,380 --> 01:09:22,380
And from there on, people will go to stores

1337
01:09:22,860 --> 01:09:25,180
just like they do nowadays

1338
01:09:25,180 --> 01:09:27,500
and will purchase these items,

1339
01:09:27,500 --> 01:09:32,180
depending on how much credit, so to speak,

1340
01:09:32,180 --> 01:09:35,700
they have coming from their work

1341
01:09:35,700 --> 01:09:38,060
within each workers council.

1342
01:09:38,060 --> 01:09:39,980
So I'm a consumer

1343
01:09:39,980 --> 01:09:44,140
and I had an annual consumption proposal

1344
01:09:44,140 --> 01:09:45,380
that's been pre-approved.

1345
01:09:46,260 --> 01:09:51,260
And so now, and I want to admit to something personally,

1346
01:09:52,260 --> 01:09:53,700
I don't shop.

1347
01:09:55,620 --> 01:09:57,900
There's only one thing I shop for,

1348
01:09:57,900 --> 01:09:59,420
I'm the cook in my family.

1349
01:10:00,420 --> 01:10:03,500
So I shop for, I go to food stores.

1350
01:10:03,500 --> 01:10:05,500
So I shop in food stores,

1351
01:10:05,500 --> 01:10:08,820
which is why I know how people shop,

1352
01:10:08,820 --> 01:10:11,700
because I don't think I've ever bought a piece of clothing

1353
01:10:11,700 --> 01:10:12,540
I've ever worn.

1354
01:10:13,340 --> 01:10:16,940
So I shop for books and I shop for food.

1355
01:10:16,940 --> 01:10:19,820
When I shop for, and when I shop for food,

1356
01:10:19,820 --> 01:10:21,620
I'm a bargain hunter.

1357
01:10:21,620 --> 01:10:24,100
So that's why I know when I go up and down the aisles,

1358
01:10:24,100 --> 01:10:27,780
I'm looking to see what the price tag on that thing is today.

1359
01:10:27,860 --> 01:10:29,860
And if it's not a sale price tag,

1360
01:10:29,860 --> 01:10:31,100
I'm gonna probably pass it up

1361
01:10:31,100 --> 01:10:32,980
and hope for something better tomorrow.

1362
01:10:32,980 --> 01:10:35,180
So that's why I know that when people shop,

1363
01:10:35,180 --> 01:10:38,500
you show them price signals and that's how they respond.

1364
01:10:39,460 --> 01:10:42,060
But the whole idea of sort of shopping

1365
01:10:43,700 --> 01:10:45,380
is really foreign to me.

1366
01:10:45,380 --> 01:10:46,900
And I had a group of students

1367
01:10:46,900 --> 01:10:49,100
who came into my office one day

1368
01:10:49,100 --> 01:10:52,060
and they said, well, we're in your class

1369
01:10:52,060 --> 01:10:55,820
and you've been talking about this participatory economy.

1370
01:10:56,740 --> 01:10:58,780
But there's just one thing that

1371
01:11:00,460 --> 01:11:03,860
we either don't understand or we don't like about it.

1372
01:11:03,860 --> 01:11:05,900
And what they said was,

1373
01:11:07,020 --> 01:11:10,180
you don't really understand the pleasures of mauling it.

1374
01:11:11,900 --> 01:11:15,300
And I thought they were saying maul, M-A-U-L.

1375
01:11:17,420 --> 01:11:19,860
And then it turned out, no, no,

1376
01:11:19,860 --> 01:11:23,780
they meant the pleasures of going to the shopping mall,

1377
01:11:23,820 --> 01:11:28,620
seeing and being seen and just deciding on the spot,

1378
01:11:28,620 --> 01:11:31,340
what do you wanna buy or not buy?

1379
01:11:31,340 --> 01:11:33,820
And I told them, I said, you're absolutely right.

1380
01:11:34,780 --> 01:11:36,700
Your dream is my nightmare,

1381
01:11:36,700 --> 01:11:40,580
being caught in a shopping mall for more than five minutes

1382
01:11:40,580 --> 01:11:43,500
it would be a death sentence as far as I'm concerned.

1383
01:11:43,500 --> 01:11:45,580
It's the last thing I'd ever wanna do.

1384
01:11:45,580 --> 01:11:50,580
But I understand, you have a reasonable demand here.

1385
01:11:50,940 --> 01:11:55,940
And so that is a question of how do you accommodate that?

1386
01:11:56,300 --> 01:11:58,780
And so the whole idea, I never thought about

1387
01:11:58,780 --> 01:12:03,580
how the goods are actually being picked up and distributed.

1388
01:12:03,580 --> 01:12:04,740
I just thought of people as,

1389
01:12:04,740 --> 01:12:06,620
well, you're going to your local food store

1390
01:12:06,620 --> 01:12:08,300
and that's how you get the food

1391
01:12:08,300 --> 01:12:10,060
that you're gonna go home and cook.

1392
01:12:11,540 --> 01:12:14,340
But there's no reason that you can't have shopping malls.

1393
01:12:15,300 --> 01:12:17,220
I remember at one point in time,

1394
01:12:17,220 --> 01:12:19,380
and I think it's still true in Cuba,

1395
01:12:19,380 --> 01:12:24,380
they used to do, they did these big displays.

1396
01:12:24,660 --> 01:12:27,740
They wanted to show people in Cuba,

1397
01:12:27,740 --> 01:12:31,460
what new kinds of goods might become soon available

1398
01:12:31,460 --> 01:12:34,340
that they hadn't been seeing for a while.

1399
01:12:34,340 --> 01:12:37,420
And so they would do these sort of demos.

1400
01:12:37,420 --> 01:12:40,700
And they would put on sort of like a fair

1401
01:12:40,700 --> 01:12:45,700
where the economic ministry was basically saying,

1402
01:12:45,780 --> 01:12:48,780
basically saying, come out to think

1403
01:12:48,780 --> 01:12:50,200
like a shopping mall thing,

1404
01:12:50,200 --> 01:12:51,820
we're gonna show you new products

1405
01:12:51,820 --> 01:12:53,780
so you're gonna see the kinds of things.

1406
01:12:53,780 --> 01:12:55,860
There's no reason that we can't,

1407
01:12:55,860 --> 01:12:58,140
those would all be good ideas.

1408
01:12:58,140 --> 01:13:02,100
But essentially my vision always was certain items

1409
01:13:02,100 --> 01:13:05,180
would get distributed to distribution centers,

1410
01:13:05,180 --> 01:13:07,540
which really are only for one neighborhood.

1411
01:13:08,740 --> 01:13:10,660
Other items is probably gonna have to cover

1412
01:13:10,660 --> 01:13:12,500
four or five neighborhoods,

1413
01:13:12,500 --> 01:13:15,300
the kinds of goods that get sent there to be distributed.

1414
01:13:15,300 --> 01:13:17,860
But I always envisioned is you're picking it up,

1415
01:13:17,860 --> 01:13:19,820
you've got your swipe card.

1416
01:13:19,820 --> 01:13:21,600
At some point along the line,

1417
01:13:21,600 --> 01:13:23,380
your swipe card starts to tell you

1418
01:13:23,380 --> 01:13:26,140
that you're actually picking up more of certain things

1419
01:13:26,140 --> 01:13:28,220
than that you had ordered.

1420
01:13:28,220 --> 01:13:29,620
Do you wanna make an adjustment

1421
01:13:29,620 --> 01:13:31,820
or is this just something that you're gonna make up for?

1422
01:13:31,820 --> 01:13:34,060
That's where the new technology really is,

1423
01:13:34,060 --> 01:13:36,660
really should help in making the adjustments.

1424
01:13:38,740 --> 01:13:41,980
But that's the kind of process that I think

1425
01:13:41,980 --> 01:13:44,680
from the point of view of a non-shopper,

1426
01:13:44,680 --> 01:13:46,880
that's about the best I can say.

1427
01:13:46,880 --> 01:13:50,440
Yeah, and I think it's quite important for many people

1428
01:13:50,440 --> 01:13:53,240
that there is some form of flexibility still

1429
01:13:53,240 --> 01:13:54,680
and that you do not,

1430
01:13:54,680 --> 01:13:59,680
that you're not hold to buying exactly the things

1431
01:14:00,020 --> 01:14:03,700
that you were thinking of at the beginning of the year,

1432
01:14:03,700 --> 01:14:06,740
but this could be done in a fashion where,

1433
01:14:06,740 --> 01:14:11,740
I don't know, if you achieve an amount of like 80 to 90%

1434
01:14:11,800 --> 01:14:13,880
of things that you already knew

1435
01:14:13,880 --> 01:14:16,440
that you will consume, this is very good.

1436
01:14:16,440 --> 01:14:20,240
And then if there rests 10 or 20% of goods

1437
01:14:20,240 --> 01:14:21,760
that you consume over the year

1438
01:14:21,760 --> 01:14:24,600
are those that are being consumed in a more dynamic

1439
01:14:24,600 --> 01:14:26,540
and flexible and spontaneous way,

1440
01:14:26,540 --> 01:14:28,480
then this is still an improvement, I guess.

1441
01:14:28,480 --> 01:14:32,360
So this doesn't have to be an either or situation.

1442
01:14:32,360 --> 01:14:35,500
I would concur, that's the way I think about it too.

1443
01:14:35,500 --> 01:14:36,720
There are two issues.

1444
01:14:36,720 --> 01:14:38,840
I mean, one is easy to take care of.

1445
01:14:38,840 --> 01:14:41,760
What if somebody during a year ends up

1446
01:14:41,760 --> 01:14:45,720
consuming less than they were,

1447
01:14:45,720 --> 01:14:49,320
I mean, the sum total social cost of what they consume

1448
01:14:49,320 --> 01:14:50,960
is less what they're approved for.

1449
01:14:50,960 --> 01:14:51,800
Well, that's easy.

1450
01:14:51,800 --> 01:14:54,120
Then it just goes into,

1451
01:14:54,120 --> 01:14:56,560
it adds to their savings and the savings account.

1452
01:14:57,560 --> 01:15:00,360
Now, what about somebody who ends up consuming more

1453
01:15:00,360 --> 01:15:02,880
than they were approved for during the year?

1454
01:15:02,880 --> 01:15:05,980
Well, in that case, they're basically borrowing.

1455
01:15:07,680 --> 01:15:10,880
And it's some, I mean, I don't think you ever have

1456
01:15:10,880 --> 01:15:13,120
to sit in judgment over us.

1457
01:15:13,120 --> 01:15:14,720
If somebody wants to save,

1458
01:15:14,720 --> 01:15:17,240
who the hell is ever gonna say no?

1459
01:15:17,240 --> 01:15:19,000
If somebody wants to borrow,

1460
01:15:19,000 --> 01:15:21,160
and oh, but you're borrowing every year

1461
01:15:21,160 --> 01:15:23,240
and you've been borrowing every year for 15 years

1462
01:15:23,240 --> 01:15:25,080
and it's kind of becoming clear

1463
01:15:25,080 --> 01:15:26,780
that you aren't really planning

1464
01:15:26,780 --> 01:15:29,320
or whether you're planning to pay it back

1465
01:15:31,180 --> 01:15:34,360
or you're just, you think you're planning to play it back

1466
01:15:34,360 --> 01:15:37,320
but it's becoming rather obvious to the rest of us

1467
01:15:37,320 --> 01:15:40,280
that you can't, somebody has to sit in judgment over this.

1468
01:15:40,280 --> 01:15:43,640
One of my daughters works for credit unions

1469
01:15:43,640 --> 01:15:46,800
and basically has, one of her jobs is

1470
01:15:46,800 --> 01:15:51,360
people taking out new car loans to buy new cars.

1471
01:15:51,360 --> 01:15:54,040
And so she's constantly watching cases where,

1472
01:15:54,040 --> 01:15:56,120
yeah, you thought you had a credible plan

1473
01:15:56,120 --> 01:15:59,080
about your payments, but in fact, you don't.

1474
01:15:59,080 --> 01:16:02,040
So I think of it more as you're still gonna have

1475
01:16:02,040 --> 01:16:04,340
something like credit unions

1476
01:16:04,340 --> 01:16:07,920
and a credit union is going to have to sort of,

1477
01:16:07,920 --> 01:16:09,240
they're gonna have to monitor

1478
01:16:09,240 --> 01:16:12,240
whether borrowing has become insincere.

1479
01:16:16,880 --> 01:16:21,160
But there's total flexibility about saving and borrowing

1480
01:16:21,160 --> 01:16:24,400
in terms of the grand sum total of what you're spending

1481
01:16:24,400 --> 01:16:27,420
in a year being different from what you proposed.

1482
01:16:27,420 --> 01:16:30,280
There's really no problem in handling that.

1483
01:16:30,280 --> 01:16:33,800
The difficulty is for particular items.

1484
01:16:33,800 --> 01:16:38,800
So if certain things, for a certain item,

1485
01:16:39,760 --> 01:16:42,320
the grand total amount that consumers

1486
01:16:42,320 --> 01:16:44,960
are taking off the shelves

1487
01:16:44,960 --> 01:16:47,640
is greater than what was planned for,

1488
01:16:47,640 --> 01:16:50,200
then we have a decision to make,

1489
01:16:50,200 --> 01:16:52,200
well, who's gonna get it and who isn't?

1490
01:16:53,760 --> 01:16:57,280
And there you would have a complicated,

1491
01:16:57,280 --> 01:17:00,000
I mean, there I think you have a somewhat complicated issue.

1492
01:17:00,000 --> 01:17:02,960
Well, I had it in my order

1493
01:17:05,440 --> 01:17:08,000
and so should I have priority over somebody

1494
01:17:08,000 --> 01:17:10,060
who didn't have it in their order.

1495
01:17:11,040 --> 01:17:12,360
And there's another issue about,

1496
01:17:12,360 --> 01:17:14,300
well, do we just also take care of this

1497
01:17:14,300 --> 01:17:15,740
by adjusting the price?

1498
01:17:16,840 --> 01:17:19,680
And in the latest book I wrote,

1499
01:17:19,680 --> 01:17:21,360
I sort of discussed these very,

1500
01:17:21,360 --> 01:17:24,500
what are the pros and cons of handling these situations

1501
01:17:24,500 --> 01:17:28,380
which will inevitably arise one way or another?

1502
01:17:28,380 --> 01:17:30,480
And I think there are some pros and cons

1503
01:17:30,480 --> 01:17:32,080
of handling it one way or another

1504
01:17:32,080 --> 01:17:34,400
and there are issues that will arise.

1505
01:17:35,320 --> 01:17:38,080
I mean, like from the tip of my head,

1506
01:17:38,080 --> 01:17:42,760
I would say like you could easily reserve some item

1507
01:17:42,760 --> 01:17:44,160
for a period of time

1508
01:17:44,160 --> 01:17:48,600
and if it's not consumed during this time period,

1509
01:17:48,600 --> 01:17:51,880
it will be free to consume for anybody else

1510
01:17:51,880 --> 01:17:54,040
who's interested in the item.

1511
01:17:54,040 --> 01:17:58,060
And then additionally, this question of pricing

1512
01:17:58,060 --> 01:18:01,880
comes into play, but that's just a side note.

